Bladesinging	KEY:Arcane Tradition ~ Bladesinging		PREMULT:1,[PRERACE:1,Elf,Half-Elf],[PRETEXT:Restricted to Elf or Half-Elf]	SORTKEY:Class	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Arcane Tradition.Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DESC:Bladesingers are elves who bravely defend their people and lands. They are elf wizards who master a school of sword fighting grounded in a tradition of arcane magic. In combat, a bladesinger uses a series of intricate, elegant maneuvers that fend off harm and allow the bladesinger to channel magic into devastating attacks and a cunning defense.	DESC:&nl; RESTRICTION: ELVES ONLY Only elves and half-elves can choose the bladesinger arcane tradition. In the world of Faerun, elves closely guard the secrets of bladesinging. Your DM can lift this restriction to better suit the campaign. The restriction reflects the story of bladesingers in the Forgotten Realms, but it might not apply to your DM's setting or your DM's version of the Realms.		ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Bladesinging ~ Training In War And Song|PREVARGTEQ:WizardLVL,2	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Bladesinging ~ Bladesong|PREVARGTEQ:WizardLVL,2	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Bladesinging ~ Extra Attack|PREVARGTEQ:WizardLVL,6	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Bladesinging ~ Song Of Defense|PREVARGTEQ:WizardLVL,10	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Bladesinging ~ Song Of Victory|PREVARGTEQ:WizardLVL,14	SOURCEPAGE:p.141

# Bladesinging
Training In War And Song	KEY:Bladesinging ~ Training In War And Song			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	DESC:When you adopt this tradition at 2nd level, you gain proficiency with light armor, and you gain proficiency with one type of one-handed melee weapon of your choice. You also gain proficiency in the Performance skill if you don't already have it.	ABILITY:Skill|AUTOMATIC|Performance	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE=ArmorProfLight	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|One-Handed Melee Weapon|1
Bladesong				KEY:Bladesinging ~ Bladesong						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	DESC:Starting at 2nd level, you can invoke a secret elven magic called the Bladesong, provided that you aren't wearing medium or heavy armor or using a shield. It graces you with supernatural speed, agility, and focus. You can use a bonus action to start the Bladesong, which lasts for 1 minute. It ends early if you are incapacitated, if you don medium or heavy armor or a shield, or if you use two hands to make an attack with a weapon. You can also dismiss the Bladesong at any time you choose (no action required). While your Bladesong is active, you gain the following benefits:	DESC:&nl;You gain a bonus to your AC equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of +1).	DESC:&nl;Your walking speed increases by 10 feet.	DESC:&nl;You have advantage on Dexterity (Acrobatics) checks.	DESC:&nl;You gain a bonus to any Constitution saving throw you make to maintain your concentration on a spell. The bonus equals your Intelligence modifier (minimum of +l).	DESC:&nl;You can use this feature twice. You regain all expended uses of it when you finish a short or long rest.
Extra Attack			KEY:Bladesinging ~ Extra Attack					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	DESC:Starting at 6th level, you can attack twice, instead of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Extra Attack ~ 1
Song Of Defense			KEY:Bladesinging ~ Song Of Defense					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	DESC:Beginning at 10th level, you can direct your magic to absorb damage while your Bladesong is active. When you take damage, you can use your reaction to expend one spell slot and reduce that damage to you by an amount equal to five times the spell slot's level.
Song Of Victory			KEY:Bladesinging ~ Song Of Victory					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	DESC:Starting at 14th level, you add your Intelligence modifier (minimum of +1) to the damage of your melee weapon attacks while your Bladesong is active.



